      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARNIES ARMY NZ (3) put the writing on the wall with back-to-back placings from second line draws before spanking his rivals at this circuit and distance last week, working early before finding the front and cruising home by nearly 22m in this grade. Draws closer to the pegs so can deliver again. KING HIT NZ (6) was well fancied at his Australian debut at Albion Park but worked and faded. Showed ability in NZ prior and is lightly-raced with upside so could be a big improver. JAYJAYBENNY (4) is in the mix following a respectable second from this barrier at his most recent appearance here. Tricky draw for KINTIRE RUSH (10) but she is going well so with even luck she is capable of playing a role again.",
